---
title: `$plugin::state()`
description: Get plugin state data.
...

~~~ .php.xmp
Plugin::state($id, $key = null, $fail = false);
~~~

Return the stored plugin states if any, otherwise, return `$fail`:

~~~ .php
$state = Plugin::state('markdown');
~~~

> **Note:** If `$key` is array, then it will going to be the alternate values of the `$state` output if some data are not available; `$fail` data value will be ignored:
>
> ~~~ .php
> $state = Plugin::state('markdown', [
>     'table_class' => 1 // add `table_class` property to `$state` if missing
> ]);
> ~~~